http://localhost/phpmyadmin/
Click New â†’ Database name: lost_doc_db
Click Create
Create tables for Found Documents (your friend focuses on found table):
CREATE TABLE found_documents (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100),
  doc_type VARCHAR(50),
  doc_number VARCHAR(50),
  contact VARCHAR(100),
  description TEXT,
  date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
Step 4: Create Database Connection File
db_connect.php
Open and paste:
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "root";
$password = "";
$database = "lost_doc_db";

$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $database);

if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}
?>
step 5; Create Homepage File;
index.php
<?php include('includes/db_connect.php'); ?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Lost & Found Document Tracker</title>
